Code in this reviewer package
-----------------------------

The novel contributions of this submission (`code/`, `benchmarking/`,
`scripts/` directories) are released for reviewer use only during the
NeurIPS 2026 review period. A permanent open-source licence
(currently planned: Apache-2.0) will be applied to the public
repository post-acceptance.

Third-party code redistributed in this package
----------------------------------------------

* `code/model/dinov3/` — distilled from Meta AI's DINOv3 reference
  implementation (Apache-2.0).
* `code/model/dinov2.py`, `code/model/dinov2_layers/` — based on
  Meta AI's DINOv2 (Apache-2.0).
* `code/model/dpt_layers/` — based on Intel ISL MiDaS / DPT
  (MIT licence).
* `code/optim/muon.py` — based on Keller Jordan's Muon
  reference (MIT licence).

Benchmark competitors are NOT redistributed here. They are pulled
on-demand by `scripts/clone_competitor_repos.sh`:

* ResDepth (Stucker & Schindler, 2022)        — MIT
* Open-Canopy (Fajwel et al., 2025)           — CC-BY-NC-4.0
* Prompt Depth Anything (Yin et al., 2025)    — Apache-2.0
* Depth Any Canopy (Rege Cambrin et al., 2024) — Apache-2.0
* Meta CHMv2                                   — CC-BY-NC-4.0

Dataset licences
----------------

See `DATA.md`. SynRS3D, OGC, and Meta CHMv2 are CC-BY-NC-4.0
(research-only). DFC18/19 carry the IEEE GRSS contest terms.
Open-Canopy is CC-BY-4.0.
